        <mxCell id="9wf3rwxTPq5aUHUrZMnI-64" value="&lt;div&gt;In JTA(jump target address) if opcode == 111, it is a JAL instr, then immediately jump&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;In case of fetch_stall, JTA will maintain its target address and jump value&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;For pc, in case of both jump1 and jump2, jump2 is given priority&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Branches are assumed not taken&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Most of the control logic is decentralized.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;jump1 is used after delay of 1 cycle to invalidate the wrong instrs entering instr aligner&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Red signals do not go through pipeline registers.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;For jump type instructions, issue buffer will send op1 = pc and op2 = 4.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 51, 51);&quot;&gt;Single register file. Copies shown just to make the diagram convenient.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;Register file has 8 read ports and 4 write ports.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;br_taken generated by each respective ALU issue buffer.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;Functional units assert validity of output. If no result computed, valid = 0. No chance of write-back conflicts.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Only valid results from CDB are written on register file and committed by ROB.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;ROB is considered busy, if it has 1 or 0 free entries&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;autosize=1;resizable=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1170" y="250" width="590" height="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="9wf3rwxTPq5aUHUrZMnI-65" value="&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 22px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Issue&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="2149" y="865" width="80" height="75" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
